object.text: Triggers Objects

Standard platform. Follows a path relative to it's starting position. The path is a JSON array of x,y offset pairs. It is often easier to calculate the tile distance and multiple by 16 to get the per pixel travel distance. Can be set to autostart and/or loop for X times when triggered. -1 loops forever. 0 Does not loop.
Toggle Path allows you to set it to manually toggle between start and end states. Good for controllable platform sections.

You can set the frame on the sprite of the 160x16.png platform with frame. Useful for creating different looks. Hurt can make the platform cause damage if it touches Solana. Useful for creating traps and obstacles.
You can set a custom sprite key and MatterJS body scale if needed. This will mostly be applicable for creating unique looking platforms.

Gates are solid platforms that you can pass the light thru and shoot thru. They have a move direction and be be set to autoclose. They also can accept a duration property for how quickly the move, and a delay for how long they wait to autoclose if that is toggled.

Lamps can trigger other trigger objects when they are activated by the Soultransfer for by Bright. They can be set to always on, a brightness radius, as well as a decay rate if you want them to slowly decay. That is a per frame rate. So a 1 would be very fast.
These objects are activated or can activate other objects. targetName is a comma delimited list of target names. Sources is currently just for notes.
Plates are activated by dark. They can bet to be single use, or to reset after a time.
Levers can be used Solana.
SwingTweens are special platforms that wing on a radius. Not used them much, but they could be fun.
Zones for triggering HUDSPEECH dialogue. See the JSON entry for more details. Speechdata is an array of speech objects.
Zone that teleports to a pixel position in the level. Zonevalue is an array of two positions. 0 is for solana, 1 is for bright. This allows for different reset places.
A zone that does damage every time it ticks. Does NOT take into account Solana invulnerability duration.
Drips liquid down from above. Still BUGGY.
Triggers a target after enough mass is in the zone.
Allows Solana to climb while in it.
Most basic zone. Triggers a target when Solana enters.
Pushes Solana in a direction.
A balanced seesaw. Can move slower or fast adjusted by the airfriction. Crates and platforms can push on it.
Rotates another object after locking onto. Right now, only can target mirrors.
Object Objects
These objects are interactive or non-interactive objects in the work.

Mirrors bounce light shots around. Can be rotated in game by bright, dark or Solana by pressing up or down. Can also be the target of gears to rotate. Set their initial rotation value in TMX. It caps at a /- 45 deg change.
Rocks have mass and can roll around. They can be crushed by grinders or by dark to release shards to give solbombs.
Crates have mass and can be picked up by Bright and carried around to stack or weight things down.
Solana can swim in water but loses energy quickly. Bright can not enter water at all. Dark can jump extra far.
Releases lightning bugs/fireflies that can provide a quick energy boost if collected.
Test Vehicle for the mines. Still a little buggy. Can crush breakable tiles.
Create object from tile. It will wobble and then fall when touched. Respawns after a short delay. TSname must match the source tilesheet in the preloader.
Create object from tile. Allows light to pass thru, but can not move past.
When hit with light, continues to shoot it at the angle it is facing. Once the light stops getting passed, teleports the shooter along the path.
Enemy Objects
Others
Generates rocks up to a certain world amount. I need to make this a local amount tracked by the rockchute, so right now, only really works with a single rockchute per level.
Creates a bunch of wheels which can push things along.
Damages Solana and destroys rocks.
Prop: Flys off when players get close.
Prop: Just inches around back and forth.
Prop: Spider climbs it's web and hides when players get close.
Prop: Panics and runs away from player when they get close. Hides in the wall. Not done ye.
Prop: Splashes particles when players step in.

Decals just create an art/animation combo. Generic. Check the preload and animations groups for what you want to do. But can be used to add ANY art to the game via TMX if the preloader and animation already exists.
Sol Crystals. Allows the unlocking of abilities. Given by bosses.

Sol Links and Sol Anchors. Are powered by bright holding down his activation button when passing thru the link. Creates a light rope/chain that can be attached to Sol Anchors to power things or act as a bridge. Will work more on this, as it is imcomplete and buggy still.
Bats fly along their path, and fire projectiles currently. The path can be manually set in the property as a JSON array or it can be a pathing layer LINE, and then referenced by pathid.
Little spikey tentacles that lurch at solana.
A large blob that will regenerate if any blips are left alive.
A mushroom that screams a sonic wave, pushing solana around. Can be used to jump higher. Shooting it disables it for a few moments.
Terrifying creatures that will hunt Solana when she is in the dark.
Unkillable, but can be stunned with shots. Will fire projectiles at solana.
A single piece of blob that bounces around until it hits Solana.

On the Exit Layer.
Exits link to Entrances. Both Solana and Bright need to be the exit IF there is not partner.
If there is a partner, Solana must be on one, and Bright on the other before it will load the next level.
In the CONFIG.JS, you must specify starting entrance names for both Bright and Solana, as well as the starting level.
Breakable tiles are painted on the breakable tile layer. They can be destroyed via a minecart or by dark.
hidden tiles are tiles that look normal, but can be passed thru. Used to create secret areas.
Chests currently spawn health when opened by Solana pressing "up"
Lines currently create a visual light path / wire effect to show things are connected and help out the player.

HOW TO MAKE A LEVEL: Create the TMX. Export the TMX to JSON.
In the preload, find the level JSON section. Add the level JSON to the preload with a name similar to the group.
Example, if the level series is m2s1, and this is the second level in the group make it m2s1b.
Copy the settings from a similar group JSON in the levelConfig.JSON file.
the current loader function is getLevelConfigByName in the CONFIG.JS file.
If it is a totally new group, there will need to be a brand new lvlcfg.JSON created.
Confirm your settings look correct and attempt to load it. Let me know if you have any issues.
HELPFUL TIP. USE THE OBJECT TYPE EDITOR (in the view menu) TO HIGHLIGHT SPECIFIC OBJECT TYPES WITH CERTAIN COLORS. MAKES QUICK REVIEW EASIER.

Hulls are a type on the hulls layer that provide the basic blocks for designing the stage. They can have a friction value, but default to 0.1 if not present. They CAN NOT BE CONCAVE. If you need a concave shape, use multiple convex ones.
